<dl id="n11124g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11124g">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11124g"> 124(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">N</font> return of the masks / Ash Wednesday / false hair / hair 2 colours</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Arrestation de Chateaubriand</b> Pendant ma promenade, je voyais rentrer les mouchards <font color="green">[police spies]</font> dans diff&eacute;rent d&eacute;guisements comme des masques le mercredi des Cendres <font color="green">[Ash Wednesday]</font> &agrave; la descente de la Courtille: ils venaient rendre compte des faits et gestes de la nuit. &hellip;. les autres &eacute;taient coiff&eacute;s de perruques sous lesquelles paraissaient des cheveux d&apos;une autres couleurs; &hellip; <br><font color="green">[Chateaubriand Under Arrest: During my walk, I saw the informers enter in different disguises <mark>like the masked figures on Ash Wednesdays on the slope of the Courtille: they were coming to report on the events and movements of the night. Some were dressed as greengrocers [...]</font> others wore wigs under which could be seen hair of another colour</mark>] <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 165</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
